 <DOC> <DOCNO>FT933-8941</DOCNO> <PROFILE>_AN-DHLCDAFEFT</PROFILE> <DATE>930812 </DATE> <HEADLINE> FT 12 AUG 93 / Commodities and Agriculture: Investors sought for Zimbabwe diamond mine </HEADLINE> <BYLINE> By KENNETH GOODING, Mining Correspondent </BYLINE> <TEXT> INVESTORS are being asked to provide money for a diamond mine near the River Limpopo in Zimbabwe, which De Beers, the South African group that dominates the diamond business, discovered but then let get away.
 The mine is River Ranch, 12km upstream from Beitbridge on the southern border of Zimbabwe.
